{"title":"Updated: New Mondraker DH Bike is Incredibly Adjustable, and Uniquely So","link":"https://bikerumor.com/mondraker-dh-bike-uniquely-adjustable-brookmacdonald/","date":1691405640000,"content":"<p><img width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/mondraker-downhill-bike-brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-2023.jpg\" alt=\"mondraker downhill bike fort william brook macdonald prototype\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/mondraker-downhill-bike-brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-2023.jpg 1600w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/mondraker-downhill-bike-brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-2023-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/mondraker-downhill-bike-brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-2023-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/mondraker-downhill-bike-brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-2023-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/mondraker-downhill-bike-brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-2023-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/mondraker-downhill-bike-brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-2023-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/mondraker-downhill-bike-brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-2023-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></p>\n<p>The MS Mondraker team are at the 2023 UCI World Champs in Fort William this weekend, riding an all-new frame design that we first spotted in <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/prototype-mondraker-dh-bike-with-multi-position-bb/\" target=\"_blank\">Lenzerheide earlier this year</a>. Now, the sock is off, revealing a new VPP suspension linkage wherein the shock is driven by the swingarm itself – not dissimilar to the layout utilized by the recently released Mondraker Neat eMTB.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/mondraker-dh-bike-prototype-fort-william-world-champs-brook-macdonald.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/mondraker-dh-bike-prototype-fort-william-world-champs-brook-macdonald-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"mondraker downhill bike fort william brook macdonald prototype drive side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/mondraker-dh-bike-prototype-fort-william-world-champs-brook-macdonald-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/mondraker-dh-bike-prototype-fort-william-world-champs-brook-macdonald-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/mondraker-dh-bike-prototype-fort-william-world-champs-brook-macdonald-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/mondraker-dh-bike-prototype-fort-william-world-champs-brook-macdonald-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/mondraker-dh-bike-prototype-fort-william-world-champs-brook-macdonald-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/mondraker-dh-bike-prototype-fort-william-world-champs-brook-macdonald-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/mondraker-dh-bike-prototype-fort-william-world-champs-brook-macdonald.jpg 1600w\" /></a><figcaption>The top tube and downtube of this prototype downhill bike are actually borrowed from the Mondraker enduro frame</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Brook MacDonald’s Prototype Mondraker Downhill Bike</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Getting a closer look at Brook MacDonald’s ride, we can see that this is one of the most uniquely adjustable downhill bikes on the World Cup circuit. In addition to chainstay length adjustment, shock mounting position adjustment, and a wide range reach adjust headset, the new frame is able to run a maximum of three cnc-machined braces on the swingarm for a multitude of different stiffness profiles, and it has a modular bottom bracket that allows for multiple BB positions. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-top-swingarm-brace-cnc-machined.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-top-swingarm-brace-cnc-machined-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"mondraker downhill bike fort william brook macdonald prototype upper cnc machined brace\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-top-swingarm-brace-cnc-machined-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-top-swingarm-brace-cnc-machined-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-top-swingarm-brace-cnc-machined-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-top-swingarm-brace-cnc-machined-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-top-swingarm-brace-cnc-machined-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-top-swingarm-brace-cnc-machined-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-top-swingarm-brace-cnc-machined.jpg 1600w\" /></a><figcaption>The top cnc-machined swingarm brace</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-middle-brace-swingarm.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-middle-brace-swingarm-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"mondraker downhill bike fort william brook macdonald prototype middle swingarm brace\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-middle-brace-swingarm-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-middle-brace-swingarm-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-middle-brace-swingarm-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-middle-brace-swingarm-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-middle-brace-swingarm-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-middle-brace-swingarm-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-middle-brace-swingarm.jpg 1600w\" /></a><figcaption>The middle cnc-machined chainstay brace; Brook runs two braces of a possible three</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-brace-plate-lower.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-brace-plate-lower-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"mondraker downhill bike fort william brook macdonald prototype bb module lower brace mount\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-brace-plate-lower-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-brace-plate-lower-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-brace-plate-lower-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-brace-plate-lower-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-brace-plate-lower-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-brace-plate-lower-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-brace-plate-lower.jpg 1600w\" /></a><figcaption>Potential for a third swingarm brace</figcaption></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This latter feature gives the team the ability to adjust effective rear-center length without impacting leverage, while simultaneously altering reach, BB height, and of course the bike’s anti-squat. No other bike, at least on the world cup circuit, has this level of adjustability.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-modular-bottom-bracket-reach-adjustment.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-modular-bottom-bracket-reach-adjustment-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"mondraker downhill bike fort william brook macdonald prototype bb module multiple positions\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-modular-bottom-bracket-reach-adjustment-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-modular-bottom-bracket-reach-adjustment-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-modular-bottom-bracket-reach-adjustment-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-modular-bottom-bracket-reach-adjustment-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-modular-bottom-bracket-reach-adjustment-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-modular-bottom-bracket-reach-adjustment-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-modular-bottom-bracket-reach-adjustment.jpg 1600w\" /></a><figcaption>The Mondraker has a removable BB module</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-removable-bb-module.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-removable-bb-module-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"mondraker downhill bike fort william brook macdonald prototype removable bb module\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-removable-bb-module-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-removable-bb-module-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-removable-bb-module-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-removable-bb-module-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-removable-bb-module-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-removable-bb-module-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-removable-bb-module.jpg 1600w\" /></a><figcaption>Here’s an alternate position BB module waiting in the wings. It has a 73mm width; 83mm is possible but the 73mm gives a better chainline.</figcaption></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Brook MacDonald’s mechanic, Jake Ireland, tells us that there is another key advantage to having a machined bottom bracket module, besides the adjustability it brings. It also gives Mondraker tighter control over the location of the BB relative to the frame pivots and dropouts, something that is absolutely critical to the kinematic. That tighter control comes from the fact that the BB isn’t part of a welded structure.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-short-chainstay-position.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-short-chainstay-position-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"mondraker downhill bike fort william brook macdonald prototype chainstay length adjust dropouts\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-short-chainstay-position-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-short-chainstay-position-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-short-chainstay-position-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-short-chainstay-position-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-short-chainstay-position-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-short-chainstay-position-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-short-chainstay-position.jpg 1600w\" /></a><figcaption>Brook runs a chainstay length of 450mm, with 460mm possible thanks to a flip-chip</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-shock-mounting-position.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-shock-mounting-position-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"mondraker downhill bike fort william brook macdonald prototype lower shock mount flip chip\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-shock-mounting-position-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-shock-mounting-position-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-shock-mounting-position-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-shock-mounting-position-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-shock-mounting-position-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-shock-mounting-position-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-shock-mounting-position.jpg 1600w\" /></a><figcaption>Three shock mount positions give three starting leverage ratios</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-reach-adjust-headset.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-reach-adjust-headset-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"mondraker downhill bike fort william brook macdonald prototype reach adjust headset\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-reach-adjust-headset-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-reach-adjust-headset-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-reach-adjust-headset-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-reach-adjust-headset-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-reach-adjust-headset-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-reach-adjust-headset-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-reach-adjust-headset.jpg 1600w\" /></a><figcaption>There is 21mm of reach adjustment, available over seven 3mm increments</figcaption></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Like the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021-mondraker-summum-races-dh-w-stealth-alloy-frame-27-5-29-wheels-or-both/\" target=\"_blank\">previous Summum DH frame</a>, the new bike runs a short-link four-bar linkage that delivers a virtual main pivot location. While the shock was previously driven by the lower link, it is now mounted to the swingarm, with three possible mounting locations giving subtly different ride characteristics. It is compressed from both ends simultaneously as the bike is pushed through its rear wheel travel.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We are told the linkage was developed with the engineers’ detailed knowledge of how the Fox DHX2 coil shock works. It has a very progressive leverage curve, and all members of the MS Mondraker Team – <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/brookmacdonald6/?hl=en\" target=\"_blank\">Brook MacDonald</a>, <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/tuhoto_ariki/?hl=en\" target=\"_blank\">Tuhoto-Ariki Pene</a> and <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/elefarinamtb/\" target=\"_blank\">Eleonora Farina</a>, were running this coil shock.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-cnc-machined-rocker-1.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-cnc-machined-rocker-1-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"brook macdonald bike check fort william world champs 2023 prototype mondraker frame cnc machined rocker fox dhx2 coil shock 500 lbs spring\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-cnc-machined-rocker-1-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-cnc-machined-rocker-1-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-cnc-machined-rocker-1-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-cnc-machined-rocker-1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-cnc-machined-rocker-1-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-cnc-machined-rocker-1-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-cnc-machined-rocker-1.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<blockquote>\n<p>“When we were testing, we found that the bikes that felt best weren’t necessarily the ones that were firing for a specific number for anti-rise, but the ones that were consistent, so they felt predictable the whole way through the travel. It is a little under 100%, and relatively consistent”</p>\n<cite>Jake Ireland, Brook MacDonald’s Mechanic</cite></blockquote>\n\n\n\n<p>We are told the mounting location doesn’t influence the overall progression of the frame, but it does alter the leverage ratio in the early phase of travel. Brook opts for the position that gives a slightly higher starting leverage ratio for a softer early stroke.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>There’s more…</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Brook’s team mate, Tuhoto-Ariki Pene is also running the new setup – his bike is sporting an <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/ochain-active-spider-offers-a-low-friction-chainless-ride-feel-with-your-chain-on/\" target=\"_blank\">OChain</a>. The OChain serves to reduce pedal kickback by dissociating rearward chainring rotation from the crankset. Brook’s bike is lacking an OChain, but his mechanic, Jake Ireland, tells us that the team is “experimenting with other methods that mean they don’t need to use an OChain”.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/mondraker-dh-bike-prototype-over-sized-e13-hub-possible-decoupler-to-reduce-pedal-kickback.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/mondraker-dh-bike-prototype-over-sized-e13-hub-possible-decoupler-to-reduce-pedal-kickback-800x534.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/mondraker-dh-bike-prototype-over-sized-e13-hub-possible-decoupler-to-reduce-pedal-kickback-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/mondraker-dh-bike-prototype-over-sized-e13-hub-possible-decoupler-to-reduce-pedal-kickback-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/mondraker-dh-bike-prototype-over-sized-e13-hub-possible-decoupler-to-reduce-pedal-kickback-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/mondraker-dh-bike-prototype-over-sized-e13-hub-possible-decoupler-to-reduce-pedal-kickback-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/mondraker-dh-bike-prototype-over-sized-e13-hub-possible-decoupler-to-reduce-pedal-kickback-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/mondraker-dh-bike-prototype-over-sized-e13-hub-possible-decoupler-to-reduce-pedal-kickback-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/mondraker-dh-bike-prototype-over-sized-e13-hub-possible-decoupler-to-reduce-pedal-kickback.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-e13-prototype-hub-t5.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-e13-prototype-hub-t5-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"brook macdonalds dh bike mondraker prototype e13 hub shell over sized possible decoupler to reduce pedal kickback\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-e13-prototype-hub-t5-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-e13-prototype-hub-t5-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-e13-prototype-hub-t5-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-e13-prototype-hub-t5-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-e13-prototype-hub-t5-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-e13-prototype-hub-t5-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-e13-prototype-hub-t5.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Intriguing.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>A closer look at the rear hub reveals a prototype from e*Thirteen. The LG1 DH carbon rim is laced to a hub shell that is over-sized on the drive side. This is not unusual in itself, but the larger diameter section looks to be even larger than that seen on e*Thirteen’s production hubs, and it looks to extend further inboard. This leads us to speculate that the new hub shell could be housing some new technology, such as a decoupler mechanism, that could prevent the rear hub from engaging during potential pedal kickback events. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>That said, we are told there are no electronics on the bike, so it’s difficult to see how exactly such a mechanism could be timed appropriately.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We reached out to E*Thirteen for comment. They say there will be more info available on this hub next year. Their comment for now is:</p>\n\n\n\n<blockquote>\n<p>“The primary design goal with that hub is to eliminate pedal kickback and it does just that. The whole MS Mondraker crew has been super helpful in helping log loads of hours and learn quite a bit”</p>\n<cite>E*Thirteen</cite></blockquote>\n\n\n\n<p>This is fairly fascinating. Depending on how exactly the technology is implemented, it could theoretically negate the need for an idler pulley on high pivot mountain bikes, removing that design constraint from future frame development projects. We look forward to learning more about how the mechanism is able to differentiate between pedaling and suspension compression-induced chain growth events.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-dh16-tire-michelin.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-dh16-tire-michelin-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"mondraker dh bike brook macdonald michelin dh16 prototype\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-dh16-tire-michelin-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-dh16-tire-michelin-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-dh16-tire-michelin-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-dh16-tire-michelin-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-dh16-tire-michelin-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-dh16-tire-michelin-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-dh16-tire-michelin.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-michelin-dh16-prototype-tire.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-michelin-dh16-prototype-tire-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"mondraker dh bike brook macdonald michelin dh16 prototype tread pattern\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-michelin-dh16-prototype-tire-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-michelin-dh16-prototype-tire-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-michelin-dh16-prototype-tire-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-michelin-dh16-prototype-tire-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-michelin-dh16-prototype-tire-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-michelin-dh16-prototype-tire-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-fort-william-world-champs-michelin-dh16-prototype-tire.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The LG1R DH carbon rim is home to a prototype Michelin DH16 tire, which is fairly similar to the Michelin Comp 16 if anyone remembers that, only better to the tune of 20 years worth of tire development. I can tell you it is intended as a dry conditions tire, it has an extraordinarily soft rubber compound, and that the MS Mondraker Team is very happy with its performance.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-mondraker-dh-prototype-renthal-fatbar-35-alloy.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-mondraker-dh-prototype-renthal-fatbar-35-alloy-800x534.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-mondraker-dh-prototype-renthal-fatbar-35-alloy-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-mondraker-dh-prototype-renthal-fatbar-35-alloy-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-mondraker-dh-prototype-renthal-fatbar-35-alloy-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-mondraker-dh-prototype-renthal-fatbar-35-alloy-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-mondraker-dh-prototype-renthal-fatbar-35-alloy-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-mondraker-dh-prototype-renthal-fatbar-35-alloy-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-pro-bike-check-mondraker-dh-prototype-renthal-fatbar-35-alloy.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-shimano-xtr-brake-lever-saint-rotors-203mm.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-shimano-xtr-brake-lever-saint-rotors-203mm-800x534.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-shimano-xtr-brake-lever-saint-rotors-203mm-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-shimano-xtr-brake-lever-saint-rotors-203mm-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-shimano-xtr-brake-lever-saint-rotors-203mm-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-shimano-xtr-brake-lever-saint-rotors-203mm-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-shimano-xtr-brake-lever-saint-rotors-203mm-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-shimano-xtr-brake-lever-saint-rotors-203mm-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/brook-macdonald-shimano-xtr-brake-lever-saint-rotors-203mm.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/sdg-gravity-saddle-with-i-beam-rails.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/sdg-gravity-saddle-with-i-beam-rails-800x534.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/sdg-gravity-saddle-with-i-beam-rails-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/sdg-gravity-saddle-with-i-beam-rails-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/sdg-gravity-saddle-with-i-beam-rails-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/sdg-gravity-saddle-with-i-beam-rails-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/sdg-gravity-saddle-with-i-beam-rails-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/sdg-gravity-saddle-with-i-beam-rails-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/sdg-gravity-saddle-with-i-beam-rails.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Brook MacDonald’s Setup</h3>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Fox 40 Factory Downhill Fork, set up firm with 97 PSI and 5 tokens</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Fox DHX2 Coil Shock, 500 lbs Spring</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Shimano XTR levers with Shimano Saint Calipers (203mm front and rear)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Tire pressures in the mid twenties</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Frame reach: 473mm (Brook is 5ft 8″ tall)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Chainstay Length: 450mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Head angle: 63°</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Bar: Renthal Fat Bar Alloy 35mm – 780mm wide</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Renthal Grips</li>\n\n\n\n<li>165mm Shimano cranks</li>\n\n\n\n<li>SDG Saddle with I-Beam rails</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://mondraker.com/wo/en\" target=\"_blank\">mondraker.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/mondraker-dh-bike-uniquely-adjustable-brookmacdonald/\">Updated: New Mondraker DH Bike is Incredibly Adjustable, and Uniquely So</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Jessie-May Morgan","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"82b10fc20b207199c61e8e97efc4a5611aa08a4d9dc6d45663475cabdc76ef60","category":"Cycling"}